GOAL:
- Define the Core public API and immutable data models.
- UI must be able to subscribe without knowing ETW details.

PUBLIC_API_TO_DEFINE:
- class CoreFacade
  - bool Start();
  - void Stop();
  - void Subscribe(callback);

DATA_MODELS:
1) VssEvent
   - timestamp
   - provider
   - event_id
   - op_type
   - volume_id (optional)
   - activity_id (optional)
   - pid (optional)
   - raw_fields

2) RequesterCandidate
   - pid
   - process_name
   - confidence_score (0.0 ~ 1.0)
   - evidence[]

3) VssTransaction
   - tx_id
   - start_time
   - end_time
   - op_type
   - volumes[]
   - result
   - requester_candidates[]
   - events[]

DESIGN_RULES:
- Core exposes read-only snapshots to UI.
- No UI headers included in Core.
- Use std::chrono for time.
- All ownership via value types or std::unique_ptr.
- Thread-safe subscription dispatch.

